article.headline: Loyola 80, Youngstown St. 68
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Blake Schilb scored a game-high 32 points Monday night to lead Loyola of Chicago to an 80-68 victory over Youngstown State. The Ramblers (14-9, 5-5 Horizon) held a 44-24 halftime lead after shooting better than 62 percent from the floor, while Youngstown State hit only 10 of their 33 shots. The Penguins (9-13, 4-6) improved their shooting in the second half, outscoring Loyola 44-36. But their first-half offensive woes allowed the Ramblers to control the entire game. Youngstown State never held the lead, nor was the game ever tied. Jajak Kou was the only other Loyola player in double figures with 19 points. Quin Humphrey led the Penguins with 23 points. Keston Roberts scored 18 points and Jack Liles added 12.
